  "name": "Bus Grammar — System Prompts for Passengers",
  "description": "32 system prompts for AI voice passengers across 6 therapeutic and archetypal 'buses': Facing Human Wreckage (Vanessa Andreotti's Hospicing Modernity), Ancestral Voices (indigenous/ecological epistemology), Jungian Archetypes (depth psychology), IFS Parts (Internal Family Systems), Chakra Voices (Hindu/yogic energy system), and DBT Mind States (Dialectical Behavior Therapy). Each prompt is designed to interpret oracle draws (tarot, I Ching, etc.) through its tradition's lens. Includes 2 Facilitator voices for synthesis across buses.\n\nPUBLIC DOMAIN ILLUSTRATION REFERENCES: Alchemical illustrations from 'Rosarium Philosophorum' (1550) and 'Atalanta Fugiens' by Michael Maier (1617) for Jungian voices. William Blake's mythological engravings (1790s-1820s) for archetypal depth. Hindu temple sculpture and tantric lotus motifs from Mughal miniatures for Chakra voices. Hokusai's 'Great Wave' and Zen enso circles for DBT mind states. Lascaux and Altamira cave paintings for Ancestral voices. Giovanni Battista Piranesi's 'Carceri d'Invenzione' (Imaginary Prisons, 1745-1761) for FHW voices — metaphor for modernity's invisible structures.",
  "grammar_type": "custom",
  "creator_name": "PlayfulProcess",
  "creator_link": "https://lifeisprocess.substack.com/",
